#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:368
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Sample /etc/samba/smb.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:369
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[global]\n"
"<comment># Replace MYWORKGROUPNAME with your workgroup/domain</comment>\n"
"workgroup = <comment>MYWORKGROUPNAME</comment>\n"
"<comment># Of course this has no REAL purpose other than letting\n"
"# everyone knows it's not Windows!\n"
"# %v prints the version of Samba we are using.</comment>\n"
"server string = Samba Server %v\n"
"<comment># We are going to use cups, so we are going to put it in here ;-)</comment>\n"
"printcap name = cups\n"
"printing = cups\n"
"load printers = yes\n"
"<comment># We want a log file and we do not want it to get bigger than 50kb.</comment>\n"
"log file = /var/log/samba/log.%m\n"
"max log size = 50\n"
"<comment># We are going to set some options for our interfaces...</comment>\n"
"socket options = TCP_NODELAY SO_RCVBUF=8192 SO_SNDBUF=8192\n"
"<comment># This is a good idea, what we are doing is binding the\n"
"# samba server to our local network.\n"
"# For example, if eth0 is our local network device</comment>\n"
"interfaces = lo <i>eth0</i>\n"
"bind interfaces only = yes\n"
"<comment># Now we are going to specify who we allow, we are afterall\n"
"# very security conscience, since this configuration does\n"
"# not use passwords!</comment>\n"
"hosts allow = 127.0.0.1 <i>192.168.1.0/24</i>\n"
"hosts deny = 0.0.0.0/0\n"
"<comment># Other options for this are USER, DOMAIN, ADS, and SERVER\n"
"# The default is user</comment>\n"
"security = share\n"
"<comment># No passwords, so we're going to use a guest account!</comment>\n"
"guest ok = yes\n"
"\n"
"<comment># Now we setup our print drivers information!</comment>\n"
"[print$]\n"
"comment = Printer Drivers\n"
"path = /etc/samba/printer <comment># this path holds the driver structure</comment>\n"
"guest ok = yes\n"
"browseable = yes\n"
"read only = yes\n"
"<comment># Modify this to \"username,root\" if you don't want root to\n"
"# be the only printer admin)</comment>\n"
"write list = <i>root</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># Now we'll setup a printer to share, while the name is arbitrary\n"
"# it should be consistent throughout Samba and CUPS!</comment>\n"
"[HPDeskJet930C]\n"
"comment = HP DeskJet 930C Network Printer\n"
"printable = yes\n"
"path = /var/spool/samba\n"
"public = yes\n"
"guest ok = yes\n"
"<comment># Modify this to \"username,root\" if you don't want root to\n"
"# be the only printer admin)</comment>\n"
"printer admin = <i>root</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># Now we setup our printers share. This should be\n"
"# browseable, printable, public.</comment>\n"
"[printers]\n"
"comment = All Printers\n"
"browseable = no\n"
"printable = yes\n"
"writable = no\n"
"public = yes\n"
"guest ok = yes\n"
"path = /var/spool/samba\n"
"<comment># Modify this to \"username,root\" if you don't want root to\n"
"# be the only printer admin)</comment>\n"
"printer admin = <i>root</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># We create a new share that we can read/write to from anywhere\n"
"# This is kind of like a public temp share, anyone can do what\n"
"# they want here.</comment>\n"
"[public]\n"
"comment = Public Files\n"
"browseable = yes\n"
"public = yes\n"
"create mode = 0766\n"
"guest ok = yes\n"
"path = /home/samba/public\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:451
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you like to use Samba's guest account to do anything concerning printing from\n"
"Windows clients: don't set <c>guest only = yes</c> in the <c>[global]</c>\n"
"section. The guest account seems to cause problems when running\n"
"<c>cupsaddsmb</c> sometimes when trying to connect from Windows machines. See\n"
"below, too, when we talk about <c>cupsaddsmb</c> and the problems that can\n"
"arise. Use a dedicated printer user, like <c>printeruser</c> or <c>printer</c>\n"
"or <c>printme</c> or whatever. It doesn't hurt and it will certainly protect you\n"
"from a lot of problems.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now create the directories required for the minimum configuration of Samba to\n"
"share the installed printer throughout the network.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create the directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mkdir /etc/samba/printer</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /var/spool/samba</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /home/samba/public</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:473
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At least one Samba user is required in order to install the printer drivers and\n"
"to allow users to connect to the printer. Users must exist in the system's\n"
"<path>/etc/passwd</path> file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:478
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the users"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:479
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>smbpasswd -a root</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(If another user is to be a printer admin)</comment>\n"
"# <i>smbpasswd -a username</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:486
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Samba passwords need not be the same as the system passwords\n"
"in <path>/etc/passwd</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:491
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You will also need to update <path>/etc/nsswitch.conf</path> so that Windows\n"
"systems can be found easily using NetBIOS:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:495
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing /etc/nsswitch.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:496
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/nsswitch.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Edit the hosts: line)</comment>\n"
"hosts: files dns <i>wins</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:504
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring CUPS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:508
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is a little more complicated. CUPS' main config file is\n"
"<path>/etc/cups/cupsd.conf</path>. It's structure is similar to Apache's\n"
"<path>httpd.conf</path> file, so many you may find it familiar. Outlined in the\n"
"example are the directives that need to be changed:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/cups/cupsd.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:515
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ServerName <i>PrintServer</i>          <comment># your printserver name</comment>\n"
"ServerAdmin <i>root@PrintServer</i>    <comment># the person for printer-related hate-mail, e.g. you</comment>\n"
"\n"
"AccessLog /var/log/cups/access_log <comment># probably doesn't need changing</comment>\n"
"ErrorLog  /var/log/cups/error_log  <comment># doesn't really need changing either</comment>\n"
"\n"
"LogLevel  debug <comment># only while installing and testing, should later be\n"
"                # changed to 'info'</comment>\n"
"\n"
"MaxClients 100 <comment># I've had to set this to 1000000000 or so because some time back,\n"
"               # there seemed to be a bug in CUPS' controlling of the web interface,\n"
"               # making CUPS think a denial of service attack was in progress when\n"
"               # I tried to configure a printer with the web interface. weird.</comment>\n"
"\n"
"BrowseAddress @IF(<i>eth0</i>) <comment># Change this to your internal net interface</comment>\n"
"\n"
"&lt;Location /&gt;\n"
"Order Deny,Allow\n"
"Deny From All\n"
"Allow From <i>192.168.1.*</i>  <comment># the addresses of your internel network\n"
"                        # e.g. 192.168.1.* will allow connections from any host on\n"
"                        # the 192.168.1.0 network. change to whatever suits you</comment>\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;Location /admin&gt;\n"
"AuthType Basic\n"
"AuthClass System\n"
"Allow From <i>192.168.1.*</i>  <comment># same as above, allow any host on the\n"
"                        # 192.168.1.0 network to connect and do\n"
"                        # administrative tasks after authenticating</comment>\n"
"Order Deny,Allow\n"
"Deny From All\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:551
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Edit <path>/etc/cups/mime.convs</path> to uncomment some lines. The changes to\n"
"<path>mime.convs</path> and <path>mime.types</path> are needed to make CUPS\n"
"print Microsoft Office document files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/cups/mime.convs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:557
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(The following line is found near the end of the file. Uncomment it)</comment>\n"
"application/octet-stream        application/vnd.cups-raw        0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:562
#, no-wrap
msgid "Edit <path>/etc/cups/mime.types</path> to uncomment some lines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:565
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/cups/mime.types"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:566
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(The following line is found near the end of the file. Uncomment it)</comment>\n"
"application/octet-stream\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:571
#, no-wrap
msgid "CUPS needs to be started on boot, and started immediately.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:574
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the CUPS service"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:575
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(To start CUPS on boot)</comment>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add cupsd default</i>\n"
"<comment>(To start or restart CUPS now)</comment>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd restart</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:584
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing a printer for and with CUPS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, go to <uri link=\"http://linuxprinting.org\">LinuxPrinting.Org</uri> to\n"
"find and download the correct PPD file for your printer and CUPS. To do so,\n"
"click the link Printer Listings to the left. Select your printers manufacturer\n"
"and the model in the pulldown menu, e.g. HP and DeskJet 930C. Click \"Show\". On\n"
"the page coming up click the \"recommended driver\" link after reading the various\n"
"notes and information. Then fetch the PPD file from the next page, again after\n"
"reading the notes and introductions there. You may have to select your printers\n"
"manufacturer and model again. Reading the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.linuxprinting.org/cups-doc.html\">CUPS quickstart guide</uri> is\n"
"also very helpful when working with CUPS.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:601
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now you have a PPD file for your printer to work with CUPS. Place it in\n"
"<path>/usr/share/cups/model</path>. The PPD for the HP DeskJet 930C was named\n"
"<path>HP-DeskJet_930C-hpijs.ppd</path>. You should now install the printer.\n"
"This can be done via the CUPS web interface or via command line. The web\n"
"interface is found at <path>http://PrintServer:631</path> once CUPS is running.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:608
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install the printer via command line"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:609
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>lpadmin -p HPDeskJet930C -E -v usb:/dev/ultp0 -m HP-DeskJet_930C-hpijs.ppd</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/cupsd restart</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:614
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Remember to adjust to what you have. Be sure to have the name (<c>-p</c>\n"
"argument) right (the name you set above during the Samba configuration!) and to\n"
"put in the correct <c>usb:/dev/usb/blah</c>, <c>parallel:/dev/blah</c> or\n"
"whatever device you are using for your printer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should now be able to access the printer from the web interface and be able\n"
"to print a test page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:628
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the Windows printer drivers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:632
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that the printer should be working it is time to install the drivers for\n"
"the Windows clients to work. Samba 2.2 introduced this functionality. Browsing\n"
"to the print server in the Network Neighbourhood, right-clicking on the\n"
"printershare and selecting \"connect\" downloads the appropriate drivers\n"
"automagically to the connecting client, avoiding the hassle of manually\n"
"installing printer drivers locally.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:641
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are two sets of printer drivers for this. First, the Adobe PS drivers\n"
"which can be obtained from <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.adobe.com/support/downloads/main.html\">Adobe</uri> (PostScript\n"
"printer drivers). Second, there are the CUPS PS drivers, to be obtained by\n"
"emerging <c>net-print/cups-windows</c>. There doesn't seem to be a difference\n"
"between the functionality of the two, but the Adobe PS drivers need to be\n"
"extracted on a Windows System since it's a Windows binary. Also the whole\n"
"procedure of finding and copying the correct files is a bit more hassle. The\n"
"CUPS drivers support some options the Adobe drivers don't.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:653
#, no-wrap
msgid "This HOWTO uses the CUPS drivers for Windows. Install them as shown:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:656
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install the drivers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:657
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge -av cups-windows</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:661
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we'll use the script <c>cupsaddsmb</c> provided by the CUPS distribution.\n"
"Be sure to read its manpage (<c>man cupsaddsmb</c>), as it will tell you which\n"
"Windows drivers you'll need to copy to the proper CUPS directory. Once you've\n"
"copied the drivers, restart CUPS by running <c>/etc/init.d/cupsd restart</c>.\n"
"Next, run <c>cupsaddsmb</c> as shown:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:668
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run cupsaddsmb"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:669
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cupsaddsmb -H PrintServer -U root -h PrintServer -v HPDeskJet930C</i>\n"
"<comment>(Instead of HPDeskJet930C you could also specify \"-a\", which will\n"
"\"export all known printers\".)</comment>\n"
"# <i>cupsaddsmb -H PrintServer -U root -h PrintServer -a</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:676
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The execution of this command often causes the most trouble. Read through the\n"
"<uri link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic.php?t=110931\">posts in this\n"
"thread</uri> for some troubleshooting tips.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:682
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here are common errors that may happen:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:687
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The hostname given as a parameter for <c>-h</c> and <c>-H</c>\n"
"    (<c>PrintServer</c>) often does not resolve correctly and doesn't identify\n"
"    the print server for CUPS/Samba interaction. If an error like: <b>Warning:\n"
"    No PPD file for printer \"CUPS_PRINTER_NAME\" - skipping!</b> occurs, the\n"
"    first thing you should do is substitute <c>PrintServer</c> with\n"
"    <c>localhost</c> and try it again.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:695
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The command fails with an <b>NT_STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL</b>. This error message\n"
"    is quite common, but can be triggered by many problems. It's unfortunately\n"
"    not very helpful. One thing to try is to temporarily set <c>security =\n"
"    user</c> in your <path>smb.conf</path>. After/if the installation completes\n"
"    successfully, you should set it back to share, or whatever it was set to\n"
"    before.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:705
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This should install the correct driver directory structure under\n"
"<path>/etc/samba/printer</path>. That would be\n"
"<path>/etc/samba/printer/W32X86/2/</path>. The files contained should be the 3\n"
"driver files and the PPD file, renamed to <path>YourPrinterName.ppd</path> (the\n"
"name which you gave the printer when installing it (see above).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:713
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pending no errors or other complications, your drivers are now installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:719
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finalizing our setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:723
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lastly, setup our directories.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "Final changes needed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:727
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mkdir /home/samba</i>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /home/samba/public</i>\n"
"# <i>chmod 755 /home/samba</i>\n"
"# <i>chmod 755 /home/samba/public</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:736
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing our Samba configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:740
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We will want to test our configuration file to ensure that it is formatted\n"
"properly and all of our options have at least the correct syntax. To do this we\n"
"run <c>testparm</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:745
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running the testparm"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:746
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(By default, testparm checks /etc/samba/smb.conf)</comment>\n"
"# <i>/usr/bin/testparm</i>\n"
"Load smb config files from /etc/samba/smb.conf\n"
"Processing section &quot;[printers]&quot;\n"
"Global parameter guest account found in service section!\n"
"Processing section &quot;[public]&quot;\n"
"Global parameter guest account found in service section!\n"
"Loaded services file OK.\n"
"Server role: ROLE_STANDALONE\n"
"Press enter to see a dump of your service definitions\n"
" ...\n"
" ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:763
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the Samba service"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:767
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now configure Samba to start at bootup; then go ahead and start it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:770
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the Samba service"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:771
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add samba default</i>\n"
"# <i>/etc/init.d/samba start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:778
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking our services"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:782
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It would probably be prudent to check our logs at this time also. We will also\n"
"want to take a peak at our Samba shares using <c>smbclient</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:786
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking the shares with smbclient"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:787
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>smbclient -L localhost</i>\n"
"Password:\n"
"<comment>(You should see a BIG list of services here.)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:797
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration of the Clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:799
#, no-wrap
msgid "Printer configuration of *nix based clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:803
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Despite the variation or distribution, the only thing needed is CUPS. Do the\n"
"equivalent on any other UNIX/Linux/BSD client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:807
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a Gentoo system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:808
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge cups</i>\n"
"# <i>nano -w /etc/cups/client.conf</i>\n"
"ServerName <i>PrintServer</i>      <comment># your printserver name</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:814
#, no-wrap
msgid "That should be it. Nothing else will be needed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:818
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you use only one printer, it will be your default printer. If your print\n"
"server manages several printers, your administrator will have defined a default\n"
"printer on the server. If you want to define a different default printer for\n"
"yourself, use the <c>lpoptions</c> command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:824
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting your default printer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:825
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(List available printers)</comment>\n"
"# <i>lpstat -a</i>\n"
"<comment>(Sample output, yours will differ)</comment>\n"
"HPDeskJet930C accepting requests since Jan 01 00:00\n"
"laser accepting requests since Jan 01 00:00\n"
"<comment>(Define HPDeskJet930C as your default printer)</comment>\n"
"# <i>lpoptions -d HPDeskJet930C</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:834
#, no-wrap
msgid "Printing in *nix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:835
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Specify the printer to be used)</comment>\n"
"# <i>lp -d HPDeskJet930C anything.txt</i>\n"
"<comment>(Use your default printer)</comment>\n"
"# <i>lp foobar.whatever.ps</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:842
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Just point your web browser to <c>http://printserver:631</c> on the client if\n"
"you want to manage your printers and their jobs with a nice web interface.\n"
"Replace <c>printserver</c> with the name of the <e>machine</e> that acts as your\n"
"print server, not the name you gave to the cups print server if you used\n"
"different names.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:852
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting a Windows or Samba share in GNU/Linux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:856
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Don't forget to install <c>net-fs/samba</c> on the client(s) that will be\n"
"accessing the shares.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:861
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now is time to configure our kernel to support CIFS. Since I'm assuming\n"
"we've all compiled at least one kernel, we'll need to make sure we have all the\n"
"right options selected in our kernel. For simplicity's sake, make it a module\n"
"for ease of use. It is the author's opinion that kernel modules are a good thing\n"
"and should be used whenever possible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:868
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:869
#, no-wrap
msgid "CONFIG_CIFS=m\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:873
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then make the module/install it; insert it with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:876
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the kernel module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:877
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>modprobe cifs</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:881
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the module is loaded, mounting a Windows or Samba share is possible. Use\n"
"<c>mount</c> to accomplish this, as detailed below:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:885
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting a Windows/Samba share"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:886
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(The syntax for mounting a Windows/Samba share is:\n"
"  mount -t cifs [-o username=xxx,password=xxx] //server/share /mnt/point\n"
"If we are not using passwords or a password is not needed)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"# <i>mount -t cifs //PrintServer/public /mnt/public</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(If a password is needed)</comment>\n"
"# <i>mount -t cifs -o username=USERNAME,password=PASSWORD //PrintServer/public /mnt/public</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:897
#, no-wrap
msgid "After you mount the share, you would access it as if it were a local drive.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:903
#, no-wrap
msgid "Printer Configuration for Windows NT/2000/XP clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:907
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"That's just a bit of point-and-click. Browse to <path>\\\\PrintServer</path> and\n"
"right click on the printer (HPDeskJet930C) and click connect. This will download\n"
"the drivers to the Windows client and now every application (such as Word or\n"
"Acrobat) will offer HPDeskJet930C as an available printer to print to. :-)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:918
#, no-wrap
msgid "Final Notes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:920
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Fond Farewell"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/quick-samba-howto.xml:924
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"That should be it. You should now have a successful printing enviroment that is\n"
"friendly to both Windows and *nix as well as a working share!\n"
